  "text": "When applying the Directed Relation Graph with Error Propagation (DRGEP), it is important to find an appropriate set of tolerances to ensure that the reduced mechanisms achieve optimal trade-offs between accuracy and efficiency. For the DRGEP method, smaller tolerances result in a larger size of reduced mechanism. [CITATION_1] In this study, the mechanism reduction process began with a set of smaller error tolerances that produced a larger size reduced mechanism and the results of this reduced mechanism were compared with the detailed mechanism for the targets of ignition delay and key species mole fractions such as TPGME and soot precursors. The process was then repeated for a larger error tolerance that generated a smaller mechanism, until the specified targets for the reduced mechanism were no longer met within acceptable error.",
